6. Another way to phrase it

Gradients are not logic gates themselves, but they create the conditions that allow logic to emerge.

You could summarize it like this:

Gradients are the physics; logic is the organized control of gradient-driven processes.

Or in your metaphor:
	•	terrain creates slopes
	•	water flows along slopes
	•	dams and channels turn flow into controlled actions

Logic gates are like hydraulic control systems built from the river.

